Today tigers are endangered, and they face high risks of extinction in the wild. Around a century ago, 100,000 wild tigers roamed freely across Asia. Now, only around 4% are left. Additionally, several tiger subpopulations are classified as extinct, including the Caspian Tiger and Bali Tiger.Their future depends only on us... the disappearance of this beautiful animal will be our irreparable, unforgivable fault…#animal #bigcat #bigcats #wildindia #nature #conservation #tiger #reelsvideo #reelsinstagram
